ume pays particular attention to both theoretical and practical forms of critical resistance work, including historical analyses of anti-racist, anti-imperialist, and anti-capitalist movements that have engaged with Bergson's writings—for example, the Négritude movement, the Indigenismo movement, and the Peruvian Socialist Party. These historical and theoretical intersections provide a timely and innovative contribution to the existing scholarship on Bergson, and demonstrate the importance of his thought for contemporary social and political issues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aArea Studies : African Studies. 4aArea Studies : French Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Postcolonial Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Social.2bisacsh1 aAl-Saji, Alia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanneken, Jaime, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeadley, Clevis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoseph-Gabriel, Annette K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawlor, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNovoa, Adriana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPitts, Andrea J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPitts, Andrea J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aShuster, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestmoreland, Mark William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestmoreland, Mark William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWhite, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle i